{"word":"ἀγριόω","slug":"ἀγριόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγριόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄγριος'><el>ἄγριος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make wild</i> or <i>savage</i>; <el>τινί</el> against one, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>ἠγριούμην</el>, aor1 <el>ἠγριώθην</el>: <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>ἠγρίωμαι</el>; <i>to grow wild</i> or <i>savage</i>, and in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <i>to be so</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in moral sense, <i>to be savage, fierce</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}